olive oil
1 packet diced bacon
1 packet garlic paste
1 pinch chilli flakes
1 packet tomato sugo
½ bottle cream
½ sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Fresh Fettuccine
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 bag parsley
1 bag spinach & rocket mix
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 bottle Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing

• Boil the kettle
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
high heat
• Cook bacon, breaking up with a
spoon, until browned, 3 mins
• Add garlic paste and a pinch of chilli
flakes (if using), cook until fragrant,
1 min
• Add tomato sugo, cream
and seasoning (1/2 sachet for 2P /
1 sachet for 4P), cook until thickened,
2-3 mins

• Pour boiling water into a saucepan
over high heat, then add a generous
pinch of salt
• Bring to the boil, then add fettuccine
and cook until ‘al dente’, 3 mins
• Transfer cooked pasta to frying pan
with a dash of pasta water and toss
to coat

• Roughly chop tomato. Thinly
slice cucumber
• In a bowl, combine tomato,
cucumber, spinach & rocket mix and
dressing. Season to taste
• Divide bacon pasta between plates
• Top with Parmesan and torn parsley.
Serve with salad